title: Grateful Dead Live at Radio City Music Hall on 1980-10-23
lineage: Master Cassettes (Nakamichi DR-1)> Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) > dBpoweramp 24/96 > Adobe Audition 3.01 > TLH flac2496
description:
Set I
On The Road Again, It Must Have Been The Roses, Dark Hollow, Jack A Roe, Cassidy, China Doll, Monkey & The Engineer, Ain't No Lie-> Ripple
Set II
Feel Like A Stranger, Tennessee Jed, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, Little Red Rooster, Big Railroad Blues, The Music Never Stopped
Set III
Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Casey Jones
Comment
First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text: Great show, sadly overlooked I was fortunate to have seen 7 of the 8 shows at Radio City and this was one of my favorites. This is a great AUD recording and brings back fond memories. The acoustic set is truly epic.  I know that many people dismiss the electric sets from this legendary tour, but this was and remains a great show. Enjoy.
